# Tweets Feature Structure Guide

The tweets feature is a core part of the application, with components in:

- [features/tweets/components/](mdc:apps/web/src/features/tweets/components): Contains Tweet UI components.
- [routes/_protected/tweets/](mdc:apps/web/src/routes/_protected/tweets): Protected routes for tweet views, including individual tweet views under [$tweetid/](mdc:apps/web/src/routes/_protected/tweets/$tweetid).
- [packages/api/src/server/router/tweet.ts](mdc:packages/api/src/server/router/tweet.ts): Contains the API routes and handlers for tweet data.

The tweets feature allows users to create, view, edit, and delete tweets. It uses the API package for data fetching and the UI package for shared components.
